  {
    "id": "work-005",
    "title": "The Ancient",
    "year": "2023",
    "type": "mixed-media",
    "series": "quantum refraction",
    "medium": "water color on rice paper, wax, salt, ink.",
    "size": "70 × 136 cm",
    "thumbnail": "img/works/The ancient.webp",
    "image": "img/works/The ancient.webp",
    "description": "The  work was inspired by H.P. Lovecraft’s short novel \"The Call of Cthulhu\". The piece reflect my ongoing curiosity about how fear and beauty coexist within my conception.In this work, I focus on the use of ink and salt on rice paper. \n\nInk, traditionally associated with Chinese landscape painting, creates a sense of vastness of natural spaces. What I aimed to capture was precisely the psychological tension one feels when confronting such immensity.\n\nThe gradual diffusion of ink suggest the aquatic quality of Lovecraftian creatures, on the other hand it also acts as  visualisation of spreading of madness frequently depicted in his works.",
    "createdAt": "2026-05-21T01:59:24+00:00",
    "media": [
      {
        "kind": "image",
        "src": "img/works/The ancient.webp"
      }
    ],
    "content": {
      "kind": "image",
      "src": "img/works/The ancient.webp",
      "poster": "img/works/The ancient.webp",
      "link": "",
      "modelFormat": ""
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "work-010",
    "title": "Cosmic",
    "year": "2025",
    "type": "mixed-media",
    "series": "quantum refraction",
    "medium": "acrylic on canvas, spray paint, sand, glitter, resin crystals, modeling paste.",
    "size": "100 × 80 cm",
    "thumbnail": "img/works/Cosmic.webp",
    "image": "img/works/Cosmic.webp",
    "description": "This piece was inspired by Fungi from Yuggoth by H.P. Lovecraft, where unknown entity dwarf human existence. By placing a colossal, god-like organism against the vastness of the universe, I  questioned humanity’s perceived significance within an indifferent cosmos. It echoes the concept of Alice Syndrome: a distortion of scale and perception reinterpreted here on a cosmic scale. The work reflects my ongoing interest in exploring how awe and fear intertwine when confronting the unknown.",
    "createdAt": "2026-05-21T02:11:50+00:00",
    "media": [
      {
        "kind": "image",
